24/08/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- A US congressional delegation, led by Republican Curt Weldon, arrived in Belgrade on Saturday (23 August) to discuss boosting economic ties and identifying investment opportunities. Serbian Prime Minister Zoran Zivkovic and Deputy Prime Minister Cedomir Jovanovic met with the delegation, which was invited by the Association of Industrialists and Entrepreneurs of Serbia-Montenegro. (Tanjug, B92, BBC - 23/08/03)
